<TITLE> 719 Barisal jail inmates to get voter ID </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Barisal, Nov 2 (bdnews24.com)  As many as 719 detainees and convicts of Barisal Central Jail are going to get voter and national ID card with photo, according to a polls official. Under a special system, the convicts would be photographed starting Saturday, district election officer Manirul Islam said. "Information on these convicts has been gathered. Their photos would be taken from Saturday until Sunday," Manirul told bdnews24.com. Jailer Syed Mustafijur Rahman said, "We have collected information on the convicts with the help of supervisors. The Election Commission has informed us that the photos of the convicts will be taken from Saturday under special system'. On why the convicts of other five districts of Barisal division were not registered as voters, Monirul said "The work of voter enlistment has started only in Barisal district of the division, the convicts of other districts would not be enlisted." He, however, said the convicts of other districts would be registered once the information collection in other districts started. Election officers said 84 convicts among the 719 came from city corporation while the rest from 10 upazilas of Barisal. bdnews24.
